---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const effective = 'July 3, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Roske.AI"
  description="Privacy policy for roske.ai. The site runs no analytics and no advertising trackers, and collects personal information only when you choose to submit it through a form."
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="effective"><strong>Effective:</strong> {effective}</p>

    <p>
      This policy covers <strong>roske.ai</strong>, the personal website of
      Edward Roske. It explains what the site collects, why, who it is shared
      with, and the choices you have. The site is a static website: it has no
      user accounts, no login, and no database of visitors.
    </p>

    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <p>
      roske.ai runs <strong>no analytics, no advertising trackers, and no
      cross-site tracking cookies</strong>. It does not sell or rent personal
      information to anyone. The only personal information it collects is what
      you choose to type into a form (a contact message, a speaking inquiry, or
      a newsletter signup), and that goes only to Edward and the service that
      delivers it.
    </p>

    <h2>What the site collects, and why</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Form submissions.</strong> If you use the contact form, the
        speaking inquiry form, or a newsletter signup box, we receive the
        information you enter (for example your name, email address, message,
        and any event details you provide). It is used only to reply to you, to
        evaluate a speaking request, or to add you to the mailing list you asked
        to join.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Newsletter email address.</strong> If you subscribe, your email
        address is stored so we can send the newsletter. You can unsubscribe at
        any time, and doing so removes you from the list.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>A theme preference.</strong> Your choice of dark or light mode
        is saved in your browser's local storage on your own device. It is not a
        tracking cookie, it never leaves your browser, and it is not sent to any
        server.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The site does <strong>not</strong> use Google Analytics, advertising
      pixels, fingerprinting, or any similar tracking technology.
    </p>

    <h2>Service providers</h2>
    <p>
      A few third parties help run the site. Each receives only what it needs to
      do its job, and each has its own privacy policy governing its handling of
      your data.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>GitHub Pages</strong> hosts the site. Like any web host, its
        servers may log standard technical information such as your IP address
        and browser type when a page is served. See GitHub's privacy statement.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Web3Forms</strong> processes form submissions and delivers them
        to Edward by email. It receives the contents of any form you submit.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The newsletter provider</strong> (currently the same form
        service, moving to Buttondown) stores your email address to send the
        newsletter you subscribed to.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Google Fonts</strong> serves the site's typefaces from Google's
        servers (fonts.googleapis.com and fonts.gstatic.com). When your browser
        requests a font, Google may receive your IP address as part of serving
        it, governed by Google's privacy policy.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Google Calendar</strong> powers the "book a call" scheduling
        links. If you follow one to book time, your scheduling details are
        handled by Google Calendar.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Embedded YouTube videos</h2>
    <p>
      Some pages embed videos using the YouTube player in privacy-enhanced mode
      (served from youtube-nocookie.com), and link to videos on Edward's YouTube
      channel. When you play an embedded video or follow a link to YouTube,
      YouTube and Google may collect information about that interaction and may
      set their own cookies, as described in their policies. This site does not
      control and does not receive that data.
    </p>
    <p>
      Your use of embedded YouTube content is subject to the
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/t/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube Terms of Service</a>
      and the
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a>.
      You can manage or delete the data Google holds about you, including data
      from embedded players, through
      <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's account settings</a>
      and, for YouTube ad settings, the
      <a href="https://safety.google/privacy/privacy-controls/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google security and privacy controls</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      roske.ai sets no cookies of its own and uses no advertising or analytics
      cookies. It stores a single dark/light theme preference in your browser's
      local storage. Third-party embeds (such as a YouTube player) may set their
      own cookies if you interact with them; those are governed by the third
      party's policy, linked above.
    </p>

    <h2>How long data is kept</h2>
    <p>
      Messages you send through a form live in Edward's email like any other
      correspondence, and are kept only as long as useful for the conversation.
      Newsletter subscriptions are kept until you unsubscribe. There is no other
      stored visitor data, because the site keeps none.
    </p>

    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Unsubscribe from the newsletter using the link in any newsletter email.</li>
      <li>
        Ask us to delete information you have sent, or ask what we hold, by
        emailing the address below. Since the site stores almost nothing, this
        is usually a quick request to handle.
      </li>
      <li>Clear the theme preference any time by clearing your browser's site data for roske.ai.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      The site is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly
      collect personal information from them.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      If this policy changes, the updated version will be published at this URL
      (roske.ai/privacy) and the effective date above will be revised.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy or about your data can be sent to
      <a href="mailto:Edward@Roske.AI">Edward@Roske.AI</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 64px 24px 96px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .prose { color: var(--color-text); }
  :global([data-theme="light"]) .prose { color: var(--color-text-dark); }
  .prose h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
  }
  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .prose h1 { color: var(--color-text); }
  :global([data-theme="light"]) .prose h1 { color: var(--color-text-dark); }
  .prose .effective { margin-bottom: 32px; }
  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .prose .effective { color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  :global([data-theme="light"]) .prose .effective { color: var(--color-text-dark-muted); }
  .prose h2 {
    margin-top: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
  }
  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .prose h2 { color: var(--color-text); }
  :global([data-theme="light"]) .prose h2 { color: var(--color-text-dark); }
  .prose ul { margin: 0 0 16px 24px; }
  .prose li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .prose p { margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .prose strong { font-weight: 700; }
  .prose a { color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .prose a:hover { text-decoration-thickness: 2px; }
</style>
